  "text": "Another promising approach for spheroid generation is the application of magnetic structuring. Recently, Lewis et al. [CITATION_1] showed that the use of superparamagnetic nanoparticles achieved magnetic levitation of MSCs within collagen 1 gels. As a result of 3 hours of incubation under external magnetic field, MSCs formed spheroids with a mean diameter of 259 μm, preserving their multipotent properties [CITATION_2] .",
